### Get all customers
GET http://localhost:5000/api/customers

### Search customers by name or phone
GET http://localhost:5000/api/customers?search=Amit

### Get customer by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/customers/<customer_id>

### Create a new customer
POST http://localhost:5000/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Amit Sharma",
    "phone": "+919999888877",
    "email": "amit.sharma@example.com",
    "address": "Flat 102, Sector 15, Noida",
    "reminderIntervalDays": 3
}

### Create another customer
POST http://localhost:5000/api/customers
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Sunita Verma",
    "phone": "+918888777766",
    "email": "sunita.v@example.com",
    "address": "45-B, Mall Road, Shimla",
    "reminderIntervalDays": 5
}

### Update customer details
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/customers/<customer_id>
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "amit.newemail@example.com",
    "address": "Flat 505, Block C, Noida Sector 62",
    "reminderIntervalDays": 10
}

### Delete customer and all their transactions
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/customers/6a1c45f740d7cc9f95e15ff6
